sections.content:
“Federal Territory Sports Council” and “State Sports Council”
mean respectively the Federal Territory Sports Council and a State
Sports Council duly established under section 7;

to advise the Minister on matters pertaining to sports
generally  and  to  the  proper  and  more  effective
implementation of the provisions of this Act;

to  co-ordinate  the  activities  in  respect  of  sports
conducted by government departments or governmental
or non-governmental agencies;

to require government departments, and governmental
and  non-governmental  agencies  dealing  in  sports  to
submit reports regarding their activities;

subject to the provision of any regulations made under
section 15, to regulate standards to be maintained by
sports enterprises;

to receive, in consideration of the services rendered by
it,  such  commission  or  payment  as  may  be  agreed
upon;

all  moneys  earned  by  the  operation  of  any
project,  scheme  or  enterprise  financed  from
the Fund;

all moneys earned or arising from any property,
investment,  mortgage,  charges  or  debentures
acquired by or vested in the Board;

“District Sport Council” means the District Sports Council set up in the State by
the State Sports Council or in the case of Federal Territory, Sabah and Sarawak, by
the Sports Council of each administrative area;

(a) to promote the general interest of sports in the state and in particular to
provide adequate facilities for the advancement of all branches of sports at
the State and District level;

(b) to  require  government  departments,  and  governmental  and  non-
governmental agencies dealing in sports to submit reports regarding their
activities;

**(b) two Deputy Chairman, who shall be appointed by the Menteri Besar or
Chief  Minister  of  the  State,  one  of  them  is  the  Secretary  of  the  State
Government;
